@startuml wiring
title Full system — boot order and runtime data flow

participant "MockSensorSource\n(or future MqttSensorSource)" as Source
participant "PlantStore" as Store
participant "handlePublish /\nAedes broker" as Broker
participant "createDatabase" as DB
participant "Express\n(/status, /history)" as HTTP
participant "Socket.IO" as WS
participant "React Native app" as App

== Boot ==
[-> DB: createDatabase(DB_PATH)
[-> Store: new PlantStore()
Store -> DB: on('state') → insertState(...)
[-> HTTP: createApp({ store, db })
HTTP -> WS: createSocketServer(httpServer, store)
Store -> WS: on('reading') → emit sensor:update
Store -> WS: on('state') → emit plant:state
[-> Broker: startBroker(PORT_MQTT, { store, db })
[-> Source: source.start()

== Runtime (mock source tick every 5 s) ==
Source -> Store: ingest({ sensor, data })
Source -> DB: insertReading({ sensor, data, at })
Store -> Store: buildSnapshot → calculatePlantState
Store -> WS: emit('state') if changed
WS -> App: plant:state { state, reason, color }
Store -> WS: emit('reading')
WS -> App: sensor:update { sensor, data, at }

== Runtime (real ESP, future) ==
note over Broker: ESP publishes to plant/sensors/*\nAedes fires 'publish' event
Broker -> Store: store.ingest(reading)
Broker -> DB: db.insertReading(...)

== REST requests ==
App -> HTTP: GET /status
HTTP -> Store: getState(), getReadings()
HTTP -> DB: getLatestWatering()
HTTP --> App: { plant, sensors, lastWatering }

App -> HTTP: GET /history?sensor=soil&period=1h
HTTP -> DB: getReadings({ sensor, since })
HTTP --> App: [{ sensor, data, at }, …]

@enduml
